  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 255 theme — abc.ABCMeta dunder method qualnames and co_consts. NEW in extra122: abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts.__len__()==1 (only the docstring); abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts[0].__class__.__name__=='str' (the sole const is a str); abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts[0].__len__()==99 (docstring is 99 chars); abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_consts.__len__()==1; abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__.__len__()==25 ('ABCMeta.__instancecheck__'); abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (cls, instance); abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_varnames[0]=='cls'; abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_varnames[1]=='instance'; abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_consts.__len__()==1; abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__qualname__.__len__()==25 ('ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__', tied with __instancecheck__); abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_argcount==2 (cls, subclass); abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_varnames[1]=='subclass'; abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_name.__len__()==17 ('__instancecheck__'); abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_name.__len__()==17 ('__subclasscheck__', tied). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts[0].__len__() == 99. The register docstring is exactly 99 chars: 'Register a virtual subclass of an ABC.\\n\\nReturns the subclass, to allow usage as a class decorator.\\n'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__.__len__() == 25. 'ABCMeta.__instancecheck__' is 25 chars: 'ABCMeta.'=8 + '__instancecheck__'=17 = 25. Tied with __subclasscheck__.__qualname__.__len__()==25 ('ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__': 'ABCMeta.'=8+'__subclasscheck__'=17=25). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ and __subclasscheck__ are Python-defined in Lib/abc.py, so their class is 'function'; they override type's built-in isinstance() and issubclass() checks. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
