invariant abc_extra122.register_co_consts_len_1:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts.__len__() == 1 — abc.ABCMeta.register has exactly one code constant: the docstring 'Register a virtual subclass of an ABC.\\n\\nReturns the subclass, to allow usage as a class decorator.\\n'; the co_consts tuple has only 1 element because register's implementation uses only function calls and attribute access (no literal integers, strings, or other compile-time constants besides the docstring); compare: __instancecheck__.__code__.co_consts.__len__()==1 (same pattern) and __subclasscheck__.__code__.co_consts.__len__()==1 (same pattern); all three abc.ABCMeta Python-defined methods have co_consts with exactly 1 entry (their docstring); register.__code__.co_argcount is 2 (cls, subclass); register.__qualname__ is 'ABCMeta.register' (len=16); NEW in extra122: first standalone ABCMeta.register co_consts length invariant in abcmetaconsts122 namespace; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: code_inspection
