  description: "abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts.__getitem__(0).__len__() == 99 — abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts[0] is the docstring 'Register a virtual subclass of an ABC.\\n\\nReturns the subclass, to allow usage as a class decorator.\\n' which is exactly 99 characters; this docstring is a str (co_consts[0].__class__.__name__ == 'str'); 99 chars = 37 chars for first line + 1 newline + 1 blank line newline + 59 chars for second sentence + 1 trailing newline; the docstring is significantly longer than __instancecheck__'s docstring ('Override for isinstance(instance, cls).' = 39 chars) and __subclasscheck__'s (39 chars); register.__code__.co_consts.__len__() is 1 (only the docstring); NEW in extra122: first standalone ABCMeta.register docstring length invariant in abcmetaconsts122 namespace; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: code_inspection
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abc.ABCMeta.register.__code__.co_consts.__getitem__(0).__len__
