invariant abc_extra122.instancecheck_qualname_len_25:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__.__len__() == 25 — abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__ is 'ABCMeta.__instancecheck__' (25 chars: 'ABCMeta.'=8 + '__instancecheck__'=17 = 25); this is tied with __subclasscheck__ for the longest method qualname in this spec (both are 25); compare qualname lengths in this spec: register=16, __instancecheck__=25 (tied), __subclasscheck__=25 (tied); the length 25 exceeds ABCMeta.__subclasshook__.__qualname__.__len__()==24 (covered in extra99) by 1 char; both __instancecheck__ and __subclasscheck__ have co_name len=17 (the method name itself is 17 chars: leading '__'=2 + body + trailing '__'=2); __instancecheck__ is Python-defined (class='function') and overrides isinstance() for ABCMeta; NEW in extra122: first standalone ABCMeta.__instancecheck__ qualname length invariant in abcmetaconsts122 namespace; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: code_inspection
