invariant abc_extra122.subclasscheck_varname1_is_subclass:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_varnames.__getitem__(1).__eq__('subclass') returns 'subclass' — abc.ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__.__code__.co_varnames[1] is 'subclass' (the second positional parameter); this distinguishes __subclasscheck__ from __instancecheck__ whose co_varnames[1] is 'instance'; 'subclass' is 8 chars while 'instance' is 8 chars — they are the same length but different names; __subclasscheck__ is called by issubclass(subclass, cls) to check if subclass is registered with or inherits from the ABC; __subclasscheck__.__code__.co_argcount is 2 (cls, subclass); __subclasscheck__.__qualname__ is 'ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__' (len=25: tied with __instancecheck__); __subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__ is 'function'; NEW in extra122: first standalone ABCMeta.__subclasscheck__ co_varnames[1] invariant in abcmetaconsts122 namespace; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3"
