invariant abc_extra122.instancecheck_co_name_len_17:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_name.__len__() == 17 — abc.ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__code__.co_name is '__instancecheck__' (17 chars: '__'=2 + 'instancecheck'=13 + '__'=2 = 17); this is tied with __subclasscheck__.__code__.co_name.__len__()==17 ('__subclasscheck__': '__'=2+'subclasscheck'=13+'__'=2=17); both dunder method names have the same 17-char length; compare with other dunder method co_name lengths in the abc spec series: '__init__'=8, '__new__'=7, '__subclasshook__'=16, '__instancecheck__'=17 (longest), '__subclasscheck__'=17 (tied); '__instancecheck__' and '__subclasscheck__' share the same 13-char body ('instancecheck' vs 'subclasscheck' — both are 13 chars); __instancecheck__.__qualname__.__len__() is 25 (qualname is 'ABCMeta.__instancecheck__'); NEW in extra122: first standalone __instancecheck__ co_name length invariant in abcmetaconsts122 namespace; wave 255; verified with Python 3.14.3"
